bled new constraints on the eccentricity\nof K2-25's orbit. We find K2-25b's orbit to be eccentric ($e>0.20$) for all\nreasonable stellar densities and independent of the observation wavelength or\ninstrument. The high eccentricity is suggestive of a complex dynamical history\nand motivates future searches for additional planets or stellar companions.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Nov 2019 19:00:04 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Wed, 15 Jan 2020 03:34:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-16"}
