s implications for the formation of filamentary\nstar-clusters. Cloud complexes formed in regions dominated by supernova\nfeedback have fewer star-forming cores, and these are more widely distributed.\nThese differences show galactic-scale forces can have a significant impact on\nstar formation within molecular clouds.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Wed, 13 Nov 2019 19:01:13 GMT"},{"version":"v2","created":"Mon, 18 Nov 2019 11:38:21 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-01-08"}
