th $m_1 > 45 \\ M_\\odot$ at\n$2.8^{+5.4}_{-2.0}\\%$ of the total merger rate. After 100 detections like those\nof O1 and O2 from a population with a maximum primary mass of $45 \\, M_\\odot$,\nit would be common for the most massive system to have an observed\nmaximum-likelihood mass $m_1 \\gtrsim 70 \\, M_\\odot$.\n","versions":[{"version":"v1","created":"Thu, 14 Nov 2019 01:10:57 GMT"}],"update_date":"2020-03-18"}
